<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1908" box="[377,495,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucografa">
<emphasis box="[377,495,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="460">leucografa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but a similar carina can be found among dark as well as among amber-winged species, since the carina of T6 is variable in shape and ornamentation in both groups.
</paragraph>
